A young woman gave birth to a healthy baby girl on a pavement
in Durban central on Monday afternoon. Paul Herbst, Medi Response spokesperson, said paramedics responded
to Durban central, for reports of a childbirth in progress. He said they found a young woman on the pavement who had
just given birth to a healthy baby girl. He said search and rescue members report that they had come
across the woman who had collapsed, and they assisted with the delivery. Herbst said the mother and baby are both healthy and have
been transported to hospital.